Name: Congenital varicella syndrome
Synonyms_List__c: Fetal effects of Chickenpox, Fetal effects of varicella zoster virus, Fetal varicella infection, Fetal varicella zoster syndrome, Varicella Embryopathy, Varicella virus antenatal infection
Disease_Description__c: A condition, whose clinical manifestations include intrauterine growth restriction, scarring cicatricial lesion of the limbs, abnormalities of the limbs, microcephaly, chorioretinitis, microphthalmia, cataracts, cortical atrophy, seizures, and evidence of damage to the autonomic nervous system, that is caused by fetal exposure to the varicella zoster virus during the first trimester of pregnancy.
